gurmukhi: golw Awid aucwr kY dwqI AMq aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN cIn cqur inrDwr ]659]
transliteration: Golaa Aadh Ouchaar Kai Daatiant Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Haincheen Chatur Nirdhaar||659||
translation: Saying the word “Golaa” in the beginning and then the word “Daatti” at the end, the names of Tupak are formed.659.

gurmukhi: golw Awid aucwr kY qjnI puin pd dyhu ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN cIn cqur icq lyhu ]660]
transliteration: Golaa Aadh Ouchaar Kai Tajanipoun(i) Pad Deh(u)|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Cheen Chatur Chit Leh(u)||660||
translation: Saying the word “Golaa” in the beginning and then adding the word “Tajni” the names of Tupak are formed.660.

gurmukhi: juAwlw Awid aucwir kY d`Cin AMq aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu sumiq svwir ]661]
transliteration: Juaalaa Aadh Oucdaar(i) Kai Dachchhan(i) Ant Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soumat(i) Savaar||661||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Jawaalaa” and then the word “Dakshini” at the end, the names of Tupak continue to be formed.661.

gurmukhi: juAwl skqnI bkqR qy piRQmY krO biKAwn ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr pCwn ]662]
transliteration: Juaal Saktanibaktra Te Prithmai Karau Bakhiaan|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Pachhaad||662||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Jawaal-shaktini” and then adding the word “Bakatra” afterwards, the names of Tupak are recognized.662.

gurmukhi: juAwlw qjxI bkqR qy piRQmY kro aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu cqur ibcwr ]663]
transliteration: Juaalaa Tajanibaktra Te Prithmai Daro Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Chatur Bichaar||663||
translation: Uttering firstly “Jawaalaa-Tajni” and then “Bakata”, the names of Tupak are formed, which may be comprehended.663.

gurmukhi: juAwlw Cwfin piRQm hI muK qy kro aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr suDwr ]664]
transliteration: Juaalaa Chhaadan(i) Pritham Himoukh Te Daro Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sudhaar||664||
translation: Uttering firstly “Jawaalaa-Chhaadani”, the names of Tupak, O wise men ! may be comprehended correctly.664.

gurmukhi: jUAwlw dwiein piRQm hI muK qy kro aucwr ]nwm qupok ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr suDwr ]665]
transliteration: Juaalaa Daain(i) Pritham Himoukh Te Daro Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sudhaar||665||
translation: O wise men ! comprehend correctly the names of Tupak by uttering firstly the word “Jawaalaa-deyani”.665.

gurmukhi: juAwlw dwiein piRQm hI muK qy kro aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr svwr ]666]
transliteration: Juaalaa Baktran(i) Pritham Himoukh Te Daro Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Savaar||666||
translation: O wise men ! comprehend correctly the names of Tupak by uttering firstly the word “Jawaalaa-bakatrani”.666.

gurmukhi: juAwlw Awid aucwr kY pRgtwien pd dyh ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN cIn cqur icq lyhu ]667]
transliteration: Juaalaa Aadh Ouchaar Kai Pragtaain Pad Deh|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Cheen Chatur Chit Leh(u)||667||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Jawaalaa” and then adding the word “Pragtaayani”, O wise men ! the names of Tupak are formed.667.

gurmukhi: juAwlw Awid aucwr kY DnxI AMq aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr svwir ]668]
transliteration: Juaalaa Aadh Ouchaar Kai Dharniant Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sadaar(i)||668||
translation: Know the names of Tupak by uttering firstly the word “Jawaalaa” and then saying the word “Dharni” at the end.668.

gurmukhi: durjn Awid aucwr kY dwhin puin pd dyhu ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN cIn cqur icq lyhu ]669]
transliteration: Durjan Aadh Ouchaar Kai Daahan(i) Poun(i) Pad Deh(u)|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Cheen Chatur Chit Leh(u)||669||
translation: The names of Tupak are comprehended by uttering firstly the word “Durjan” and then adding the word “Daahani”.669.

gurmukhi: dRujnwid Sbducir kY drrin AMq aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr suDwr ]670]
transliteration: Drujanaadh Shabadouchar(i) Kai Dau-ran(i) Ant Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sudhaar||670||
translation: Comprehend the names of Tupak correctly by firstly uttering the word “Durjan” and saying the word “Dalni” at the end.670.

gurmukhi: golI DrxI bkqR qy piRQmY kro aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hyoq hYN lIjhu suGr suDwr ]671]
transliteration: Golidharnibaktra Te Prithmai Daro Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sudhaar||671||
translation: The names of Tupak are formed by uttering firstly the word “Goli-dharani and then the word “Bakatra”.671.

gurmukhi: duSt Awid Sbd aucwr kY dwhin bhur aucwr ]nwm qupk ky hoq hYN lIjhu suGr suDwr ]672]
transliteration: Dousht Aadh Shabad Ouchaar Kai Daahan(i) Bahur Ouchaar|| Naam Toupak Ke Hot Hain Leejoh Soughar Sudhaar||672||
translation: By uttering firstly the word “Dusht” and then word “Dahani” after-wards, the names of Tupak are formed, which O wise men ! you may comprehend.672.
